Encoding (and compressing) videos with ffmpeg

```bash
# Install in Ubuntu based distros
sudo apt install ffmpeg 

# Compress
# crf -> lower values is more quality
# codec -> libx265 is better than libx264 but yet less used in devices
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vcodec libx265 -crf 28 output.mp4 

## For WhatsApp Web (use codec libx264)
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vcodec libx264 -acodec aac output.mp4

## Without Audio (flag -an)
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vcodec libx265 -crf 28 -an output.mp4

## Cutting video based on time
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -ss 00:02:45 -t 00:09:40 -vcodec libx265 -crf 28 -an output.mp4
```
